reviewText: 2 great Julia Roberts movies presented in a convenient format.  I really like it.

The only reason I didn't give these movies 5 stars is because of some of the excessive foul language. But, if you don't have kids or if you ever have time to curl up with a good movie alone, these two are great! Roberts' characters are so down to earth/realistic in these films. They are both hilarious movies and you may shed a tear or two if you're a "softy" like me!

''Steel Magnolias' is one of my most favorite movies ever. And getting 'My Best Friends' Wedding' as a bonus is ever better.

The Best Cancer surviving movies ever. My daughter and I both have had cancer and laughed, then cried, then came to the realization that we were going to be ok. We still watch this movie and even though we are hundreds of miles apart we can still adlib many parts, especially the "take a whack at Wheezer" lines. This is the best movie ever!!

Movie is a classic.  It will make you laugh and make you shed a few tears.

Steel Magnolias is an excellent movie with many of my favorite actors. I have had this film for years in my own video library, and have viewed it numerous times. I purchased this movie as a present for my daughter-in-law, and she loved it, too. Shirley McClaine is hilarious, Sally Fields is excellent,  The entire staff performed wonderfully!  It has always made me laugh out loud, and cry openly.  I would recommend this movie to any woman (or man) who enjoys romance and tragedy, as well as comedy.

My Best Friend's Wedding is not as good, but is an enjoyable "chick flick".  Worthy of watching.
